Commentary Text: T Natarajan to Samson, FOUR, hey you! How did you squeeze that yorker for four? The bowler did no wrong there. That was a base of off stump yorker, Samson backed away and sliced it, short third man was inside and it escaped past the dive. Mega finish from Sanju. Took Nattu for a six and two fours, no wonder he wanted to deny Hetmyer strike and Hety now hugs his captain for the finish

Commentary Text: Bhuvneshwar to Buttler, out Lbw!! Oh dear! He misses a hundred by a mere five runs. We had Shubman Gill not completing a hundred in the first game today, now Buttler. He throws his head back in disappointment and walks off. Bhuvi does what he never tried last over - to bowl at the stumps and it gets him a massive wicket. Bhuvi went for the killer yorker, clearly Buttler wasn't expecting anything close to his body having seen what Bhuvi was trying last over. Buttler fell over on the flick and you can clearly see him standing a long way across the line expecting a wide line again. Hats off to Bhuvi for outsmarting a set batter. Ump thought going down leg, Bhuvi immediately demanded a review. Ball-tracker said impact in line and smashing base of leg stump. Buttler walks off to a great ovation. Buttler lbw b Bhuvneshwar 95(59) [4s-10 6s-4]

Commentary Text: Sandeep Sharma to Abdul Samad, SIX, Abdul Samad, take a bow!! SRH have kept the faith in him for so long and today he wins them a game under immense pressure... This was once again the attempted yorker, slightly undercooked and right in the slot for Samad to stay deep in the crease and launch over the bowler's head for a flat six. Anti climatic to the core, SRH claim a thriller. This is the highest chase ever by SRH, highest chase at this venue as well.

Commentary Text: Kuldip Yadav to Glenn Phillips, out Caught by Hetmyer!! Phew, everyone in pink can breathe a bit easier now. Kuldip Yadav wins the battle finally but he has Hetmyer to thank for this one. A slot ball outside off, was there for Phillips to smoke out of the ground once again but he toe-ends it. Might have landed between two fielders as Hetmyer from point and Jaiswal from deep extra went for it. Hetmyer extended his arms and plucked out the catch. Commentary Text: Chahal to Anmolpreet Singh, out Caught by Hetmyer!! Ah! Yuzi Chahal is bowling within the stumps and getting turn. We didn't see that quite often in the last few games. Is he also coming back to form like Buttler? Is this the game that RR get their mojo back. Classic leggie dismissal this. Fullish ball, teases the batter for a slog-sweep, just enough turn to catch the outside half of the bat. Flies high and deep mid-wicket runs in to take an easy catch. Chahal is thrilled. Anmolpreet Singh c Hetmyer b Chahal 33(25) [4s-4 6s-1]
